ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, regardless of whether they are interested in political economy (I wasn't as interested going in, but not am quite interested), it is great training for what we'll be doing the rest of our lives...
Empirical political economy.Would recommend it to anyone doing political economy, public finance or development, as it nicely complements these fields

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Taught about not just evaluating articles, but how to discuss them with others,do referee reports, do presentations, write an article... pretty much everything! So I'd say it probably contributed a lot.
It surveyed the literature in my chosen field of interest, and gave me some ideas for research projects
